    <!-- LLD Quick Reference -->
    <section id="sec-lld" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span>🏗</span> LLD Quick Reference
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <!-- Parking Lot -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 p-5 space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal uppercase tracking-wider">Parking Lot Design (Common LLD)</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Entities:</strong> ParkingLot → ParkingFloor → ParkingSpot → Ticket → Vehicle → Payment</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Key patterns:</strong> Strategy (pricing per vehicle type), Observer (spot availability), Factory (vehicle from type string)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Concurrency:</strong> <code class="bg-card px-1 rounded text-saffron">ConcurrentHashMap&lt;SpotId, AtomicBoolean&gt;</code> — use <code class="bg-card px-1 rounded text-saffron">compareAndSet(false, true)</code> for atomic allocation.</p>
          <pre class="text-xs bg-card rounded-lg p-3 overflow-x-auto text-emerald-400 leading-relaxed">// 3 patterns in 15 lines
class ParkingLot &#123;
  private final Map&lt;SpotType, Deque&lt;ParkingSpot&gt;&gt; available
      = new ConcurrentHashMap&lt;&gt;();

  public Optional&lt;Ticket&gt; park(Vehicle v) &#123;
    return available.getOrDefault(v.spotType(), new ArrayDeque&lt;&gt;())
      .poll()
      .map(spot -&gt; Ticket.create(spot, v,
          pricingStrategy.calculate(v)));
  &#125;
&#125;</pre>
        </div>
        <!-- LRU Cache -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 p-5 space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal uppercase tracking-wider">LRU Cache Design</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Java shortcut (interview acceptable):</strong> <code class="bg-card px-1 rounded text-saffron">new LinkedHashMap&lt;&gt;(cap, 0.75f, true)</code> with <code class="bg-card px-1 rounded text-saffron">removeEldestEntry</code> override.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Custom O(1):</strong> HashMap&lt;Key, DLLNode&gt; + Doubly-Linked List. HashMap → O(1) lookup; DLL → O(1) move-to-front and evict-tail.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Distributed LRU:</strong> Redis with <code class="bg-card px-1 rounded text-saffron">maxmemory-policy allkeys-lru</code>. Add TTL for time-based expiry on top.</p>
          <div class="rounded-lg p-3 bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-500/20">
            <p class="text-xs text-blue-400"><strong>LLD Interview Flow:</strong> State entities → define interfaces → pick patterns → address concurrency → discuss trade-offs. Never jump straight to code.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HLD 6-Step Framework -->
    <section id="sec-hld" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span>🏛</span> HLD 6-Step Framework
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 p-5">
          <ol class="space-y-3">
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">1</span><strong class="text-foreground">Requirements (5 min)</strong> — Functional + Non-functional (QPS, latency SLA, availability %, consistency, durability). Write on board.</li>
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">2</span><strong class="text-foreground">Estimation (3 min)</strong> — QPS (peak = avg × 2-3×), storage/record × records/day × retention, bandwidth. Anchor on powers of 10.</li>
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">3</span><strong class="text-foreground">API Design (3 min)</strong> — Core REST endpoints. Method, path, key request/response fields. Idempotency key on POST mutations.</li>
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">4</span><strong class="text-foreground">Data Model (5 min)</strong> — Core entities, schema, SQL vs NoSQL justification. Partition key choice.</li>
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">5</span><strong class="text-foreground">High-Level Design (15 min)</strong> — Draw components + data flow. Client → LB → API Gateway → Services → DB + Cache + Queue. Show read and write paths separately.</li>
            <li class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"><span class="inline-block w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold text-center leading-6 mr-2">6</span><strong class="text-foreground">Deep Dive (15 min)</strong> — Pick 2-3 hardest problems. Scaling, consistency trade-offs, failure handling, observability. Show you know the trade-offs.</li>
