        <!-- 02 WhatsApp Duplicates -->
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 cursor-pointer select-none hover:bg-card/80 transition-colors list-none">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">02</span>
            <div class="flex-1"><p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">WhatsApp Users Receive Duplicate Messages</p><p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Idempotency · At-Least-Once · Kafka Retries · Redis Dedup</p></div>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-muted-foreground text-xs">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2 border-t border-border/20 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Root Cause:</strong> Kafka guarantees at-least-once delivery. On consumer crash after processing but before offset commit, message is redelivered. Network retries cause the same issue.</p>
            <div class="mermaid text-xs">
sequenceDiagram
  participant C as Client
  participant WS as WebSocket
  participant K as Kafka
  participant Con as Consumer
  participant R as Redis Dedup
  C->>WS: send(msgId=abc123)
  WS->>K: publish(message)
  K-->>Con: deliver [at-least-once]
  Con->>R: SETNX senderId:abc123
  alt First delivery
    R-->>Con: 1 - new
    Con->>Con: persist + notify
    Con->>K: commitOffset
  else Duplicate
    R-->>Con: 0 - exists
    Con-->>Con: drop silently
    Con->>K: commitOffset
  end
            </div>
            <pre class="text-xs bg-card rounded-lg p-3 overflow-x-auto text-emerald-400 leading-relaxed">@KafkaListener(topics = "messages", containerFactory = "factory")
public void consume(Message msg, Acknowledgment ack) &#123;
    String key = msg.getSenderId() + ":" + msg.getClientMsgId();
    Boolean isNew = redis.opsForValue()
        .setIfAbsent(key, "1", 24, HOURS);
    if (Boolean.TRUE.equals(isNew)) &#123;
        messageRepository.save(msg);
        notifyRecipient(msg);
    &#125;
    ack.acknowledge(); // always commit offset
&#125;</pre>
