        <!-- 04 BookMyShow Double Booking -->
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 cursor-pointer select-none hover:bg-card/80 transition-colors list-none">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">04</span>
            <div class="flex-1"><p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">BookMyShow Sells the Same Seat Twice</p><p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Optimistic Locking · SELECT FOR UPDATE · Race Condition · Distributed Lock</p></div>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-muted-foreground text-xs">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2 border-t border-border/20 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Root Cause:</strong> Two users simultaneously check seat availability — both see it free, both book it. Classic lost update problem with no locking.</p>
            <div class="mermaid text-xs">
sequenceDiagram
  participant U1 as User 1
  participant U2 as User 2
  participant DB as Database
  U1->>DB: SELECT status FROM seats WHERE id=A1 → FREE
  U2->>DB: SELECT status FROM seats WHERE id=A1 → FREE
  U1->>DB: UPDATE seats SET status=BOOKED, user=U1 WHERE id=A1
  U2->>DB: UPDATE seats SET status=BOOKED, user=U2 WHERE id=A1
  Note over DB: BOTH succeed! Seat sold twice ❌
            </div>
            <pre class="text-xs bg-card rounded-lg p-3 overflow-x-auto text-emerald-400 leading-relaxed">// Fix 1: SELECT FOR UPDATE (pessimistic lock)
@Transactional
public Booking book(String seatId, String userId) &#123;
    Seat seat = seatRepo.findByIdWithLock(seatId); // SELECT FOR UPDATE
    if (seat.getStatus() != FREE) throw new SeatUnavailableException();
    seat.setStatus(BOOKED);
    seat.setUserId(userId);
    return bookingRepo.save(new Booking(seat, userId));
&#125;

// Fix 2: Optimistic lock (high contention = many retries, use with caution)
@Version long version; // JPA optimistic lock
// UPDATE ... WHERE id=? AND version=? — fails if version changed</pre>
            <p class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-500/20 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><strong>Deeper:</strong> For IPL finals (10K concurrent users on one seat), use Redis distributed lock: SETNX seat:A1:lock with 30s TTL. Lock holder proceeds; others poll or fail-fast. Avoids DB contention entirely.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 05 Netflix Buffering -->
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 cursor-pointer select-none hover:bg-card/80 transition-colors list-none">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">05</span>
            <div class="flex-1"><p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Netflix Buffers Right After New Season Drops</p><p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">CDN Pre-warming · Adaptive Bitrate · Cache Thundering Herd</p></div>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-muted-foreground text-xs">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2 border-t border-border/20 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Root Cause:</strong> New content not pre-warmed in CDN edge caches. First million users all trigger CDN-miss → origin pull → origin overwhelmed. ABR quality drops as origin throughput degrades.</p>
            <div class="mermaid text-xs">
flowchart LR
  R([Release]) -->|push| ORIG[Origin\nS3 / Media Server]
  ORIG -->|pre-warm| CDN["CDN Edge\n(Global PoPs)"]
  U([Users]) -->|request| CDN
  CDN -->|cache hit| U
  CDN -->|miss only| ORIG
  style CDN fill:#1A2230,stroke:#17C492,color:#ECE8FF
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Fix:</strong> Pre-warm CDN before release. Push video segments to all edge PoPs 30 min before premiere. Use adaptive bitrate (HLS/DASH) — client auto-downgrades quality under load. Netflix Open Connect (their own CDN) goes further: ISP-deployed appliances cache content days before release.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 06 Uber Surge -->
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 cursor-pointer select-none hover:bg-card/80 transition-colors list-none">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 text-saffron text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">06</span>
            <div class="flex-1"><p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Uber Surge Pricing During Rain</p><p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Geospatial Indexing · Real-time Aggregation · H3 Hexagons</p></div>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-muted-foreground text-xs">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2 border-t border-border/20 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Problem:</strong> Computing surge multiplier requires knowing demand/supply ratio per geographic cell in real-time. Naïve approach: per-request DB query with geo radius search — too slow at scale.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Fix:</strong> Uber uses H3 hexagonal grid (Uber open source). Each driver pings location every 4 sec → Kafka → stream processor aggregates supply per H3 cell → Redis. Demand comes from ride request rate per cell. surge = demand/supply ratio, pre-computed every 30 sec.</p>
            <pre class="text-xs bg-card rounded-lg p-3 overflow-x-auto text-emerald-400 leading-relaxed">// H3 cell for a GPS coordinate (resolution 9 ≈ 174m hexagon)
String cell = H3Core.getInstance().latLngToCellAddress(lat, lng, 9);
// Redis: INCR supply:cell:&lt;h3id&gt; on driver update
// Redis: INCR demand:cell:&lt;h3id&gt; on ride request
// Surge worker: poll every 30s, compute ratios, store in Redis</pre>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 07 Amazon Cart Stale -->
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card/50 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 cursor-pointer select-none hover:bg-card/80 transition-colors list-none">
