            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Root Cause:</strong> Brute-force cosine similarity over 10M+ vectors is O(n·d) — too slow for real-time search. Embedding the query itself adds latency.</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground"><strong class="text-foreground">Fixes:</strong> (1) ANN (Approximate Nearest Neighbor) with HNSW index — O(log n) vs O(n). pgvector, Pinecone, Qdrant use HNSW. (2) Cache embeddings for popular queries. (3) Pre-filter: use keyword search (BM25) to narrow candidates, then vector re-rank. (4) Dimensionality reduction (PCA) — fewer dimensions = faster similarity.</p>
            <pre class="text-xs bg-card rounded-lg p-3 overflow-x-auto text-emerald-400 leading-relaxed">-- pgvector with HNSW index (fast ANN)
CREATE INDEX ON documents
  USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops)
  WITH (m = 16, ef_construction = 64);

-- Hybrid search: keyword pre-filter + vector re-rank
SELECT id, content,
  ts_rank(to_tsvector(content), query) AS keyword_score,
  1 - (embedding &lt;=&gt; $1) AS vector_score
FROM documents,
  plainto_tsquery($2) AS query
WHERE to_tsvector(content) @@ query  -- keyword filter
ORDER BY vector_score DESC LIMIT 10; -- vector re-rank</pre>
